1
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,480
You two,

2
00:00:14,704 --> 00:00:15,960
besides causing trouble,

3
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:17,120
what else can you do?

4
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:19,920
What's wrong?

5
00:00:20,030 --> 00:00:20,920
You tell me!

6
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,070
See for yourselves.

7
00:00:22,070 --> 00:00:22,670
Read it.

8
00:00:22,670 --> 00:00:23,280
What happened?

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,230
Chinese Police Chief

10
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:32,300
assaults British Priest in public.

11
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,220
=Cases Between Us=

12
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:36,320
Mute Devil Girl is arrested.

13
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:37,390
=Episode 22=

14
00:00:37,390 --> 00:00:39,750
Police abuse arrests,
undermining international relations.

15
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:45,390
They're twisting the facts, Sir.

16
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:46,224
Can't you see that?

17
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,600
They're twisting everything?

18
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,470
Yeah.

19
00:00:48,470 --> 00:00:49,560
Do you have any proof?

20
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:50,430
Do you?

21
00:00:50,430 --> 00:00:51,390
If we can question Pans,

22
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:52,640
the truth will come out.

23
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,470
Question him?

24
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:54,600
He's been released.

25
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,600
How can you let him go?

26
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:57,390
He's our prime suspect.

27
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:59,280
Who's the commissioner here,
you or me?

28
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:00,848
You're questioning my decision now?

29
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:03,390
You never learn.

30
00:01:03,390 --> 00:01:04,840
He's British.

31
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:06,070
The embassy demanded his release.

32
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:07,120
You had no evidence.

33
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:09,680
What was I supposed to do?
Hold him anyway?

34
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:11,230
You two!

35
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:12,640
Jeez.

36
00:01:14,016 --> 00:01:15,040
One more thing.

37
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:17,400
Listen,

38
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,590
don't even think
about working this case.

39
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,040
Starting today,

40
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:22,710
you're suspended.

41
00:01:22,710 --> 00:01:23,710
Reflect on yourself.

42
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:47,940
(Jingshi Police Department)

43
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,280
You're giving up on the case?

44
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:01,680
How am I supposed to investigate?

45
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,424
I know the I Ching, Liuyao, and Bagua.

46
00:02:03,472 --> 00:02:04,710
I read a divination for you.

47
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,580
You'll have your badge back
in a couple of days.

48
00:02:06,790 --> 00:02:07,950
You don't have to cheer me up.

49
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,470
I'll give you a ride.

50
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:10,870
No, thanks.

51
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,870
Leave me alone.

52
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:24,520
Didn't I say

53
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,750
leave me alone?

54
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,430
I'm hungry.

55
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,190
I want some noodles.

56
00:03:28,190 --> 00:03:29,930
You can have your peace.
I won't disturb you.

57
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:30,720
I'll eat my noodles.

58
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,470
Seriously?

59
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,360
Go to a restaurant or go home.

60
00:03:34,630 --> 00:03:35,590
Why come to my place?

61
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:36,750
Look,

62
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,430
now I've got to lecture you.

63
00:03:38,432 --> 00:03:39,264
A good bowl of noodles

64
00:03:39,296 --> 00:03:41,940
is all about the right time,
the right place, and the right company.

65
00:03:41,952 --> 00:03:42,560
For some reason,

66
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,672
I've been craving the zhajiangmian
made in your house.

67
00:03:44,688 --> 00:03:46,400
No one's made it better
since I was a kid.

68
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,336
Probably the God of Kitchen
blesses this place.

69
00:03:48,352 --> 00:03:49,150
I won't disturb you.

70
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,120
Enjoy your own peace.

71
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,400
I'll eat and leave.

72
00:04:13,168 --> 00:04:14,910
I was wondering
what happened to those dogs

73
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:15,860
from the dog meat shop.

74
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,264
Turns out you're keeping one of them.

75
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,750
What about the other two?

76
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,390
I gave them to Yang Dezhi.

77
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,584
His daughter likes dogs.

78
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,510
I thought you never kept pets.

79
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,040
Why keep this one?

80
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,680
This one just wouldn't leave.

81
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,360
Dogs understand people.
He can understand us.

82
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,000
Looks like

83
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,160
you're quite fond of dogs.

84
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,416
Dogs are loyal.

85
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:45,070
Once they choose someone,
they're with them for life.

86
00:04:45,430 --> 00:04:46,720
Mine are all hunting dogs, though.

87
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,310
Magnificent.

88
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,000
I'll show you sometime.

89
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,480
Your dog won't even sniff this wine.

90
00:04:55,552 --> 00:04:57,560
I'll send over a few cases
of Romanée-Conti.

91
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,560
No need.

92
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,160
I don't drink alone.

93
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,360
Ever think about me?

94
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:06,480
This is my house.

95
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,870
Why do you keep coming here?

96
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,630
Don't you get lonely living by yourself?

97
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,390
So much for my good intentions.

98
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,120
Down you go.

99
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:17,720
Come on.

100
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,560
You're heavy.

101
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:22,480
You're raising a dog

102
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,120
that can't bark.

103
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,070
If...

104
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,070
Just suppose

105
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,390
your suspension sticks,

106
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:33,830
what will you do then?

107
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,430
Whatever my title,

108
00:05:40,896 --> 00:05:42,240
the first thing I'll do

109
00:05:42,272 --> 00:05:43,680
is find out how my mother died.

110
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,120
Once I've repaid what I owe her,

111
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,270
I'll join the army

112
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,920
and drive those imperialist scoundrels

113
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,070
out of China.

114
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,870
What about you?

115
00:05:56,630 --> 00:05:57,310
Me?

116
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,310
Yeah.

117
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,390
For example,

118
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:00,800
getting married,

119
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:01,920
having children,

120
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,070
or getting a promotion.

121
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,390
You don't have

122
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:05,776
any of the dreams
most people do?

123
00:06:07,390 --> 00:06:07,950
You do?

124
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:09,160
Of course I do.

125
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,270
Well,

126
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,480
I hope my father lives a long life,

127
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,480
and my mother stays forever young.

128
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:18,360
As for my sister,

129
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:20,630
if she doesn't want to marry,
she shouldn't have to.

130
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,310
Though I'd rather she move out.

131
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,390
Or I could.

132
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,240
I'll spend a few years as a policeman,

133
00:06:27,632 --> 00:06:28,600
and then write books.

134
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,190
Different kinds of crickets in Beijing.

135
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:35,510
Many styles of Ming furniture.

136
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:39,630
The history and development
of Chinese lacquerware.

137
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,480
There are so many things

138
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,040
I can document.

139
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,480
If I don't do it,

140
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,430
who will?

141
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,190
So...

142
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,870
you've never thought that way?

143
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,870
Before graduation, our professor told us

144
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:19,000
our class had been born

145
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,750
into the wrong era.

146
00:07:21,888 --> 00:07:24,190
One day, we'd end up facing
one another on the battlefield.

147
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,830
He left us with one thing,

148
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,190
"I have nothing to offer but blood,

149
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:30,560
toil,

150
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,310
tears and sweat."

151
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:36,040
"I have nothing to offer

152
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:38,510
but blood,

153
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:43,160
toil, tears and sweat.

154
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,000
That became the creed I live by.

155
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,510
So...

156
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,310
I'd never thought

157
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,592
about having dreams of my own.

158
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,040
What about now?

159
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,560
Young Master!

160
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:19,920
You were right.

161
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,070
There was something hidden

162
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:22,400
inside the coffin's false bottom.

163
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:27,040
Chief Yuan,

164
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:28,750
congratulations.

165
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:31,240
Good things come to those who wait.

166
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,840
Let go!

167
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,360
Bring him in.

168
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,360
You can't arrest me
whenever you feel like it.

169
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:46,960
You'd better have evidence next time.

170
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,670
Don't worry.

171
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:49,840
If we're arresting you,

172
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,550
all the paperwork is in order.

173
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,080
Yang DeZhi.

174
00:08:52,896 --> 00:08:53,780
Pull down his trousers.

175
00:08:53,808 --> 00:08:55,780
- Hold him down over there.
- What are you doing?

176
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,600
I condemn you in the name of the Lord!

177
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,790
Let me go!

178
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,360
I condemn you in the name of the Lord!

179
00:09:03,790 --> 00:09:04,550
What are you doing?

180
00:09:04,736 --> 00:09:05,960
Don't pull down my trousers.

181
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,480
Hold still.

182
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:07,080
Shameless.

183
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:07,510
Keep still.

184
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,870
I condemn you in the name of the Lord!

185
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:11,790
There it is.

186
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:12,840
His buttocks.

187
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:15,510
Get up.

188
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:21,790
Lord.

189
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,720
Please

190
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:27,030
save your faithful servant.

191
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,000
Save yourself first.

192
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,320
Wen is only 1.4 meters tall.

193
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:34,480
How did she stab you in the butt?

194
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,080
We have our own version of the story.

195
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,670
Care to hear it?

196
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,030
After escaping the fire,

197
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,200
you ran outside

198
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,550
and saw Dong Zhi run away.

199
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,030
He went to the backyard.

200
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:52,150
The mummy Li Siqiao saw

201
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:54,320
was Dong Zhi trying to escape.

202
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,720
Before he could cry for help,

203
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,008
you knocked him unconscious,

204
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,720
and dragged him back inside.

205
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,790
You smashed his face
with a heavy dictionary.

206
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:13,870
Then staged it

207
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:15,960
to look like the bookcase
had crushed him.

208
00:11:19,408 --> 00:11:21,080
After that, you set the fire again,

209
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,200
burning the body beyond recognition.

210
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:24,630
Then

211
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:28,000
you dealt with the only eyewitness,

212
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,440
Director Li's daughter.

213
00:11:29,504 --> 00:11:30,700
(Lost Dog)
The lost dog poster

214
00:11:30,710 --> 00:11:32,736
(No. 7, Dayu Alley)
gave away where she lived.

215
00:11:32,740 --> 00:11:33,390
The next morning,

216
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:35,790
you intercepted Ms. Zhang
while she was out buying groceries.

217
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:38,190
(The Law Tolerates No Deception)
Whether by threats or bribery,

218
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:41,270
you persuaded her to drug Siqiao.

219
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,270
Young Lady,

220
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:00,390
your soup is ready.

221
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,120
Where is your evidence?

222
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,030
Where is the witness?

223
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,416
Where have you hidden Ms. Zhang?

224
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:07,440
I don't know what you're saying.

225
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:09,960
Fine.

226
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,000
I gave you a chance to confess.

227
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,790
You chose not to take it.

228
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,270
Come in.

229
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,630
Allow me to introduce.

230
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:28,840
Zhao Wan'er,
the chief reporter of Ta Kung Pao.

231
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:31,390
Hello, Father.
I've heard a great deal about you.

232
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:32,360
Have a seat.

233
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:34,704
Don't you enjoy

234
00:12:34,704 --> 00:12:37,240
using newspaper reports
to pressure the police?

235
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,320
Well then.

236
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:39,520
We'll be publishing

237
00:12:39,568 --> 00:12:41,320
some important information ourselves.

238
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,480
We'll let the world see

239
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,200
how a distinguished British citizen

240
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,870
committed atrocities
against Chinese people

241
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,150
on Chinese land.

242
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,240
After Ms. Zhang drugged Siqiao,

243
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,150
as promised,

244
00:12:58,510 --> 00:13:01,120
she went to the church that afternoon.

245
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,200
Father,

246
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:16,200
are you sure they won't find out?

247
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:17,630
Father,

248
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:20,480
my employer works
for the Police Department.

249
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,750
God bless you.

250
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:35,360
That morning,

251
00:13:35,670 --> 00:13:38,440
you held a simple funeral for Dong Zhi.

252
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:40,960
So the coffin was still at the church.

253
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:43,080
The hearse was due to take it

254
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:47,080
to Anhe Cemetery that afternoon.

255
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,480
No one knew

256
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,120
that you'd secretly nailed

257
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:51,910
Ms. Zhang's body

258
00:13:59,872 --> 00:14:01,790
beneath the false bottom of the coffin.

259
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:07,940
(Dong Zhi)

260
00:14:12,544 --> 00:14:13,910
That's why when Captain Yuan

261
00:14:13,910 --> 00:14:15,030
searched your church

262
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:16,200
and even your hotel,

263
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:18,200
including the basement

264
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,030
and cold storage,

265
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:21,480
they found nothing.

266
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,790
Before,

267
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:30,510
our accusations
were only suspicions.

268
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,670
But now we have Ms. Zhang's body

269
00:14:32,736 --> 00:14:33,910
and your fingerprints.

270
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,120
Even the embassy

271
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,670
won't be able to save you now.

272
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:39,790
Right,

273
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,080
Dr. Carter?

274
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:55,630
Of these three dogs,

275
00:14:56,192 --> 00:14:57,750
one had its vocal cords removed,

276
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,270
just like Maomao.

277
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,200
The other two were lethargic,

278
00:15:01,232 --> 00:15:02,000
had poor appetites,

279
00:15:02,010 --> 00:15:04,280
and showed symptoms
of hyperactivity and frequent urination.

280
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,720
Their X-rays revealed

281
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,200
surgical changes

282
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,390
in the sella region.

283
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,270
Their pituitary glands

284
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:11,030
were removed.

285
00:15:12,030 --> 00:15:13,120
The pituitary gland?

286
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,630
Once it's removed,

287
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,720
they'll never grow again.

288
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,320
And I suspect

289
00:15:25,968 --> 00:15:27,870
he performed
the same operation on Dong Zhi.

290
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:31,840
A pituitary removal
is done through the nasal cavity,

291
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,360
opening the nasal septum
to reach the sphenoid sinus.

292
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:36,320
That's why Dong Zhi's face

293
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,390
was wrapped in bandages.

294
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,120
Such a specialized procedure.

295
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,510
Was he a doctor?

296
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:48,080
Pans' real name is Carter.

297
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,840
He was a doctor in Britain.

298
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:50,870
His own son

299
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:52,510
had a congenital pituitary deficiency

300
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:54,440
and stopped growing
at the age of ten.

301
00:15:54,768 --> 00:15:55,888
In an attempt to save his son,

302
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:57,664
he came to China
to conduct experiments.

303
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:59,550
At first, he bought dogs.

304
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,510
Later, he bought homeless children

305
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:02,840
for a few silver coins

306
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:05,270
and removed their pituitary glands.

307
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:06,600
Wen and Dong Zhi

308
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,480
were called his adopted children,

309
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:10,304
but in truth,
they were his test subjects.

310
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,600
Without prior authorization,

311
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,576
you chose to make the arrest
because you feared

312
00:16:14,576 --> 00:16:15,488
the suspect would flee

313
00:16:15,504 --> 00:16:17,550
and that more children could be harmed?

314
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,320
Yes.

315
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:22,200
My actions were improper,

316
00:16:22,304 --> 00:16:24,320
and I'd like to apologize to the public
for that.

317
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:31,840
Chief Yuan.

318
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:32,550
Look over here.

319
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,440
Dong Zhi could've escaped.

320
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:48,870
Why did he stay

321
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:50,200
to save those puppies?

322
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:57,750
(He'd undergone surgery, too.)

323
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,960
In Li Siqiao's drawing,

324
00:17:00,992 --> 00:17:03,360
the bandages covered a large part
of Dong Zhi's body.

325
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,750
His surgical wound
must've become infected.

326
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:18,830
He knew he didn't have long to live.

327
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,830
That's why he asked you

328
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:22,240
to lock Pans inside

329
00:17:23,070 --> 00:17:24,960
so he could die together
with that monster,

330
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:26,720
right?

331
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:43,620
(End of Episode 22)

332
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,640
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

333
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,180
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

334
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,430
♪However, the world changes♪

335
00:17:48,430 --> 00:17:50,350
♪You'll still be by my side♪

336
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:52,040
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

337
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,610
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

338
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:55,180
♪If this is my final chapter♪

339
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:57,680
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
